1
00:00:08,090 --> 00:00:09,800
EVERY MASCULINE GENDER OF
THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA SHALL

2
00:00:09,880 --> 00:00:11,260
FAITHFULLY PERFORM
MANDATORY MILITARY SERVICE,

3
00:00:11,340 --> 00:00:14,180
AS PRESCRIBED BY THE CONSTITUTION
OF THE REPUBLIC OF KOREA AND THIS ACT

4
00:00:14,260 --> 00:00:17,970
ARTICLE 3 OF THE MILITARY SERVICE ACT

5
00:00:19,140 --> 00:00:20,060
[man] Hey.

6
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:23,770
You know that tunnel
that we always run through?

7
00:00:23,850 --> 00:00:26,020
[soldiers chanting]
When we joined the special duty team

8
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,020
[instructor shouts]

9
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:29,270
[soldiers] My heart was beating

10
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:30,190
[instructor shouts]

11
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:32,860
[soldiers]
When I received airborne training

12
00:00:32,940 --> 00:00:35,450
I thought I was dead

13
00:00:35,530 --> 00:00:37,820
[man] There's an air-raid shelter
beneath that tunnel.

14
00:00:38,370 --> 00:00:41,330
It's actually an underground tunnel
dug out by the North Koreans.

15
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:42,330
[scoffs]

16
00:00:42,410 --> 00:00:43,830
Isn't that crazy?

17
00:00:44,660 --> 00:00:48,290
If a war breaks out,
we'll be hiding in a tunnel

18
00:00:48,380 --> 00:00:51,460
that the North dug out
with the purpose to infiltrate this place.

19
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:55,090
It's just so fucking absurd.

20
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,260
But never mind the fucking war.

21
00:00:59,350 --> 00:01:00,510
I might die before then.

22
00:01:01,430 --> 00:01:04,180
We're training every single night.

23
00:01:05,310 --> 00:01:06,480
[sighs]

24
00:01:08,730 --> 00:01:09,770
Don't you agree?

25
00:01:11,690 --> 00:01:12,780
Don't you?

26
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:14,860
I agree, sir.

27
00:01:15,530 --> 00:01:20,990
MILITARY POLICE

28
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:22,160
Right.

29
00:01:22,870 --> 00:01:28,460
I saw something interesting
while I was on leave.

30
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:36,010
[man]
"Cho Suk-bong, the rising star of judo."

31
00:01:36,090 --> 00:01:37,970
Is this really you?

32
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:40,350
Yes, sir.

33
00:01:40,430 --> 00:01:41,890
[laughs]
Hey.

34
00:01:41,970 --> 00:01:46,350
Then how did you end up
becoming such a nerdy loser? Huh?

35
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:48,690
I'm sorry, sir.

36
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:50,810
All of a sudden?

37
00:01:52,650 --> 00:01:53,940
Forget that.

38
00:01:55,110 --> 00:01:57,110
Let's see you put on a show again.

39
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:03,450
Why are you zoning out?

40
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:05,750
The anti-aircraft missile, you punk.

41
00:02:07,290 --> 00:02:08,370
Get ready.

42
00:02:18,970 --> 00:02:21,390
[man] Buddy Fucker 1, ready to fire!

43
00:02:26,220 --> 00:02:27,230
What are you doing?

44
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,730
Start jerking off, you bastard.

45
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:40,110
[theme music plays]

46
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:04,850
♪ Since I've been dreaming for too long ♪

47
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:11,730
♪ I can't find the reasons to move on ♪

48
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:17,820
♪ Wake up to reality ♪

49
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:21,110
♪ Realize we're getting old ♪

50
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:24,490
♪ All our goals ♪

51
00:03:24,570 --> 00:03:28,160
♪ Are breaking down ♪

52
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,710
[alarm blares]

53
00:03:45,090 --> 00:03:49,430
EPISODE 4: THE MONTY HALL PROBLEM

54
00:03:50,350 --> 00:03:54,020
565 DAYS UNTIL DISCHARGE

55
00:03:55,690 --> 00:03:59,230
-[video game plays on cell phone]
-[sighs]

56
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:04,200
What are you doing here?
How did you get out?

57
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,410
Where's Mom?

58
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:07,240
[Jun-ho's sister]
She went to get Dad's stuff.

59
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:12,160
He didn't hit her.

60
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:14,670
What about Dad?

61
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:16,130
[grunts]
Who knows?

62
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:18,630
He probably got drunk and fell.

63
00:04:20,170 --> 00:04:22,090
-What about your eyebrows?
-What?

64
00:04:25,590 --> 00:04:27,010
Gosh.

65
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:29,260
-I swear I'll kill you.
-You should go. I'll stay.

66
00:04:29,890 --> 00:04:31,270
Tell Mom not to come.

67
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:33,020
[door opens]

68
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,480
[sighs]

69
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:45,700
[men chattering on TV]

70
00:04:54,290 --> 00:04:55,870
Hey.

71
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:56,960
Yes?

72
00:04:58,630 --> 00:05:00,040
Do you have money?

73
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:02,960
Do you?

74
00:05:05,090 --> 00:05:06,010
[woman] Excuse me.

75
00:05:07,010 --> 00:05:09,350
Can you tell your father
to lower the volume?

76
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:10,930
He won't listen to us.

77
00:05:11,010 --> 00:05:11,890
Lady.

78
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:15,390
This punk isn't my kid.

79
00:05:18,900 --> 00:05:21,610
-[dad] She's getting on my goddamn nerves.
-I'm sorry.

80
00:05:21,690 --> 00:05:23,150
[woman] My goodness.

81
00:05:24,110 --> 00:05:25,360
[Jun-ho sighs]

82
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:27,570
[Jun-ho's dad] Hey.

83
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:30,530
Do you have money or not?

84
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,160
If you don't, just go.

85
00:05:36,160 --> 00:05:38,120
Who did you beat up this time?

86
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:41,250
[chattering on TV continues]

87
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:45,210
And what about you? Huh?
[chuckles]

88
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:48,430
Aren't you too low in rank
to be beating people up?

89
00:05:49,090 --> 00:05:52,180
The military is a mess these days.

90
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,730
Dad.

91
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:59,150
One day, when you die,

92
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:02,110
I swear I'll be laughing out loud.

93
00:06:02,190 --> 00:06:04,730
[men chattering on TV]

94
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:10,410
Sure. You do that.

95
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,580
[cell phone buzzes]

96
00:06:16,450 --> 00:06:18,040
That sounds great.

97
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,750
CORPORAL HAN HO-YEOL

98
00:06:20,830 --> 00:06:22,960
BABE, COME HOME
WE'RE HAVING PORK BELLY

99
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,380
[engine revs]

100
00:06:27,670 --> 00:06:28,930
[Jun-ho grunts]

101
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:34,560
[in English] Hi, Jun-ho.

102
00:06:35,140 --> 00:06:36,470
[in Hangul] What are you…

103
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,520
[Jun-ho's mother] Son.

104
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:41,400
-Come and have some meat.
-[Jun-ho's sister] Get over here.

105
00:06:43,770 --> 00:06:44,730
Gosh.

106
00:06:44,820 --> 00:06:47,740
I ran by the wharf and saw him there.

107
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:50,280
So I tackled him, and he just fell.

108
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,860
[all laugh]

109
00:06:51,950 --> 00:06:55,790
[Ho-yeol] I bet Private An and I
were married in our previous lives.

110
00:06:56,370 --> 00:06:58,750
Huh? We're amazing partners. Right, babe?

111
00:06:58,830 --> 00:07:00,210
[sister groans]

112
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:01,870
That's gross.

113
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:03,920
Jun-ho, you're lucky.

114
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:06,920
You can grow your hair
and use your cell phone in the army.

115
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,130
Just eat your food.

116
00:07:09,260 --> 00:07:11,970
It's not dangerous, is it?

117
00:07:12,050 --> 00:07:13,220
[Ho-yeol] Not at all.

118
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,890
Maybe it's because Private An used to box,

119
00:07:15,970 --> 00:07:18,060
but he takes good care of his body.

120
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,520
And most importantly, he has me.

121
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,890
[Ho-yeol and sister laugh]

122
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,230
[mother] Thank you.

123
00:07:24,730 --> 00:07:28,400
Please continue
to take good care of Jun-ho.

124
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,400
Don't mention it.

125
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:32,530
I've always wondered
where Private An got his good looks

126
00:07:32,610 --> 00:07:34,490
and intelligence.

127
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:36,490
I guess it was you.

128
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:37,870
[all laugh]

129
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:42,580
-[Ho-yeol] Gosh, that's hot!
-[mother] My goodness.

130
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:44,750
-Jun-ho! What's with you?
-Are you okay?

131
00:07:45,420 --> 00:07:47,130
You should get changed.

132
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,420
You're right.

133
00:07:51,220 --> 00:07:53,380
[Jun-ho] What are you doing at my house?

134
00:07:53,470 --> 00:07:54,930
[Ho-yeol] You didn't answer my calls.

135
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:58,600
Is there another deserter?

136
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:01,060
Lots of guys are on leave.
They won't come back.

137
00:08:01,770 --> 00:08:04,190
Let's say goodbye and leave.
We need to get going.

138
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,860
We can just leave right away.

139
00:08:07,650 --> 00:08:09,230
We should at least say goodbye.

140
00:08:09,940 --> 00:08:11,070
There's no need.

141
00:08:12,820 --> 00:08:13,910
Hey, Jun-ho.

142
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:17,870
You haven't said a single word
to your mother since you got here.

143
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:21,870
[mother] Jun-ho.

144
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,330
Aren't you coming in?

145
00:08:25,670 --> 00:08:27,960
Ma'am, I'm really sorry.

146
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,840
Something urgent came up,
so we need to get going.

147
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:32,630
Ah.

148
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:34,680
Really?

149
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,430
We'll be off now.

150
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:38,470
Say goodbye to your mother.

151
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:47,400
Take good care of yourself.

152
00:08:48,190 --> 00:08:49,070
And…

153
00:08:50,690 --> 00:08:52,150
be nice to those deserters.

154
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,740
-They're in a rough spot.
-Why aren't you asking me?

155
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:01,200
Why I don't come home
whenever I'm on leave.

156
00:09:04,540 --> 00:09:06,460
Why I never write back to your letters.

157
00:09:08,420 --> 00:09:09,630
[mother sighs]

158
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:13,590
I just figured you were busy. I thought…

159
00:09:13,670 --> 00:09:14,920
And why don't you…

160
00:09:22,850 --> 00:09:23,980
just run away?

161
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:32,440
Don't say that.

162
00:09:35,530 --> 00:09:37,280
Don't skip your meals.

163
00:09:38,740 --> 00:09:39,990
Forget it.

164
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:42,030
Just take it.

165
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,210
I should go now.

166
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:50,380
"I'll see you again."

167
00:09:51,380 --> 00:09:52,670
You're allowed to say that.

168
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,430
[Beom-gu] Are you on your way?

169
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:08,690
What's with Ho-yeol?

170
00:10:08,770 --> 00:10:10,940
If I get stressed,
I'll get urinary stones.

171
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:13,610
Do you want to see me die or what?

172
00:10:14,730 --> 00:10:16,280
[woman] Look at your face.

173
00:10:17,570 --> 00:10:18,570
[Jun-mok sighs]

174
00:10:18,650 --> 00:10:21,240
[woman] Aren't you going to greet
your mom? We haven't met in ages.

175
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:24,740
Jun-mok.

176
00:10:25,950 --> 00:10:28,870
You can start over again.

177
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:32,500
Those guys who bullied you
will be tried in court and be punished…

178
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:33,790
Mom, are you dumb?

179
00:10:37,630 --> 00:10:39,380
This country isn't like that.

180
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:46,930
The guys who made me wear a gas mask
are being transferred.

181
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,230
They're going to a different unit.

182
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,230
They won't become convicts

183
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:55,360
or go to jail.

184
00:10:56,780 --> 00:11:00,740
They'll just be sent somewhere else
as if nothing happened.

185
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:04,990
Excuse me.

186
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:08,370
You're high in rank, right?

187
00:11:08,450 --> 00:11:09,330
Me?

188
00:11:09,910 --> 00:11:11,120
Is this true?

189
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,920
We're carrying out
a thorough investigation.

190
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:18,130
We're not sure about the trial yet.

191
00:11:20,050 --> 00:11:22,260
Does that mean there might not be a trial?

192
00:11:22,930 --> 00:11:24,390
That's just wrong!

193
00:11:24,470 --> 00:11:25,930
Ma'am, the thing is…

194
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:30,180
He joined the army to protect the country,
but he was beaten and harassed.

195
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:32,140
That's why he deserted!

196
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:33,850
[Jun-mok] Mom, that's enough.

197
00:11:33,940 --> 00:11:36,900
Why isn't anyone taking responsibility?

198
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:41,320
-[Jun-mok] Please, mom…
-[mother] Say something, will you?

199
00:11:42,030 --> 00:11:43,700
[speaks Hangul]

200
00:11:45,410 --> 00:11:47,330
Well…
[clicks tongue]

201
00:11:47,990 --> 00:11:49,790
The military judge will hold the trial.

202
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:55,920
And the judge…

203
00:11:56,920 --> 00:12:02,050
surely won't reach a verdict

204
00:12:02,130 --> 00:12:05,220
merely for the interest of a certain unit

205
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,390
or personnel.

206
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:09,720
Nor should he be able to.

207
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:18,150
[mother] See? What did I tell you?

208
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:20,360
The world has changed.

209
00:12:21,650 --> 00:12:24,490
It'll all work out.

210
00:12:25,530 --> 00:12:29,950
My life's become a lot easier
thanks to you two.

211
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,790
I mean, we live in a different age.

212
00:12:32,370 --> 00:12:35,330
The military police
need to be careful of human rights

213
00:12:35,420 --> 00:12:38,590
and have to make sure
not to offend the soldiers.

214
00:12:38,670 --> 00:12:40,750
This won't help us
develop strong soldiers.

215
00:12:41,340 --> 00:12:43,590
It'll only weaken
the discipline of the military.

216
00:12:43,670 --> 00:12:46,930
If a war breaks out, we won't have
what it takes to carry out a mission.

217
00:12:52,810 --> 00:12:53,770
[commander sighs]

218
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:56,230
But our unit is different.

219
00:12:56,810 --> 00:12:59,650
You two are doing a great job.

220
00:12:59,730 --> 00:13:02,030
And it makes me feel very reassured.

221
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:04,900
And that guy who snores.

222
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:06,740
What was his name again, Captain Lim?

223
00:13:07,410 --> 00:13:09,160
Ah. It's Private Choi Jun-mok.

224
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,490
[commander] Yes, Choi something.

225
00:13:10,990 --> 00:13:13,290
We decided to keep things quiet

226
00:13:13,370 --> 00:13:15,960
about what happened in his unit,
so keep that in mind.

227
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:17,830
But isn't the issue a bit too serious…

228
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,460
Right.

229
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:26,590
I heard the general there
is being promoted soon.

230
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,260
You taught me another lesson, sir.

231
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,810
Captain Lim.

232
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:36,940
Yes?

233
00:13:39,730 --> 00:13:42,230
You really need to watch what you say.

234
00:13:42,820 --> 00:13:45,440
Who do you think you are
to talk out of your ass like that?

235
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:49,660
I'm sorry, sir.

236
00:13:50,370 --> 00:13:53,370
A captain makes decisions
for the entire organization.

237
00:13:54,370 --> 00:13:55,540
[commander] Do you understand?

238
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,830
-Yes, sir.
-[commander] Drink up.

239
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:07,420
-[alarm blares]
-[mysterious music plays]

240
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:17,430
[man] We were really startled too.

241
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:20,770
The guys searched the mountain all night
but couldn't find him.

242
00:14:20,850 --> 00:14:23,400
Did you notice anything unusual?

243
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:24,530
Oh.

244
00:14:25,110 --> 00:14:27,240
Our unit is directly controlled
by the army corps.

245
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:30,030
So it's very important
to keep things clean.

246
00:14:30,110 --> 00:14:31,320
You know how it is.

247
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:33,740
We train them hard,
so they're too tired to bully anyone.

248
00:14:33,830 --> 00:14:35,910
If anyone loses it,
they might shoot someone.

249
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,330
He was a sergeant,
so no one really messed with him.

250
00:14:38,410 --> 00:14:40,500
And he was picked as a model soldier
two times.

251
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:43,090
Were there any soldiers
who had issues with Sergeant Heo

252
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:45,130
or frequently got into arguments with him?

253
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:46,670
Right.

254
00:14:47,260 --> 00:14:48,510
[comrade 1] Sergeant Heo…

255
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:52,260
still owes some money at the PX.

256
00:14:52,340 --> 00:14:55,600
Chi-do really loved money.

257
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:59,770
He tore his shoulder muscle,
but he still insisted on rappelling.

258
00:15:00,350 --> 00:15:01,560
"Rappel"?

259
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:06,360
We do helicopter rappel training
four times a year.

260
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:10,860
The soldiers get paid 155,000 won
for training as it's dangerous.

261
00:15:10,950 --> 00:15:13,370
Gosh, I don't know where he spends
all his money.

262
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:17,290
We gathered our paychecks and made a bet.-

263
00:15:17,370 --> 00:15:18,620
What kind of a bet?

264
00:15:19,830 --> 00:15:22,000
[comrade 2] All sorts of stuff.

265
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:25,090
Soccer. Yut. Guessing who'd come
first place in The Music Trend.

266
00:15:25,170 --> 00:15:27,250
The medical officer warned Chi-do

267
00:15:27,340 --> 00:15:32,180
that he could severely hurt his arm
if he rappelled.

268
00:15:32,260 --> 00:15:34,390
[Chi-do's captain chuckle]
But this is what he said.

269
00:15:35,180 --> 00:15:36,850
"What's the probability of that?"

270
00:15:36,930 --> 00:15:39,850
Sergeant Heo was the one
who started the bets.

271
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,140
And he always took everything.

272
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:45,060
What do you mean?

273
00:15:45,940 --> 00:15:49,190
Oh, well…

274
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:52,950
Sergeant Heo never lost a bet.

275
00:15:55,410 --> 00:15:58,490
[comrade 1] Sergeant Heo,
are you a professional gambler?

276
00:15:58,580 --> 00:16:01,330
By any chance,
is your father Heo Yeong-man?

277
00:16:01,410 --> 00:16:04,250
-"The hand is faster than the eye."
-[comrade 2 sighs]

278
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:07,590
I always keep a close watch,
but you always win.

279
00:16:09,420 --> 00:16:11,550
I told you we should stop earlier.

280
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:15,090
How did you get four of a kind?

281
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:17,850
[comrade 2 sighs]

282
00:16:17,930 --> 00:16:18,850
Hey.

283
00:16:19,890 --> 00:16:22,310
You can never beat me.

284
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:25,060
Do you know why?

285
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:27,820
Look.

286
00:16:28,860 --> 00:16:30,110
There are three doors.

287
00:16:32,190 --> 00:16:34,780
[Chi-do] If you open the right door,

288
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:37,700
you get a six-day leave.

289
00:16:37,780 --> 00:16:39,030
Yeong-sik, pick a door.

290
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:45,370
Okay. Yeong-sik picked door number one.

291
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:50,340
But then, he finds out
that door number three isn't it.

292
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:53,380
Then let me ask you one more time.

293
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:57,800
Yeong-sik, will you stick
with door number one?

294
00:16:57,890 --> 00:17:00,390
Or will you switch to door number two?

295
00:17:05,730 --> 00:17:08,610
I'll just stick with the first one.
I don't want to switch.

296
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:09,730
Why not?

297
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:11,610
Because I might trick you?

298
00:17:12,110 --> 00:17:14,280
Or because you don't want to switch
to the wrong door?

299
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:17,200
Gosh, either way, it's a 50-50 chance.

300
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:18,280
It's one or the other.

301
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:19,370
[Chi-do] Do you think so?

302
00:17:20,370 --> 00:17:23,450
[deep inhale]
Okay. Here's the answer.

303
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:27,120
[soldiers shout]

304
00:17:28,210 --> 00:17:29,460
[soldiers speak Hangul]

305
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:32,380
[Ho-yeol]
They do that just for 150,000 won?

306
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:34,760
[Jun-ho] Of course.

307
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:38,220
My monthly pay is 122,500 won.

308
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,340
I would never.

309
00:17:39,430 --> 00:17:41,390
Even if they paid me 468,000 won.

310
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:42,350
Never.

311
00:17:43,140 --> 00:17:46,730
So he used all that money
he worked so hard to save up

312
00:17:46,810 --> 00:17:48,190
and just vanished.

313
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:50,520
"Vanished"?

314
00:17:50,610 --> 00:17:52,860
Yes, he just took off.

315
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:55,690
You'd have to be crazy to run away
when you're in the middle of nowhere.

316
00:17:56,610 --> 00:17:59,160
But he seems to be quite rational
from what we heard.

317
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:00,160
No.

318
00:18:00,870 --> 00:18:04,120
I wouldn't say he's rational.
There's something about him.

319
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:06,040
He was pretty determined too.

320
00:18:07,830 --> 00:18:09,250
What do you mean?

321
00:18:09,330 --> 00:18:12,000
Okay, listen. Jeong Hyeon-min
went on leave

322
00:18:12,090 --> 00:18:14,380
and didn't return out of impulse

323
00:18:14,460 --> 00:18:16,880
because he was having fun
playing games and drinking.

324
00:18:16,970 --> 00:18:18,800
But this guy was determined enough

325
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:21,600
to climb over a barbed wire fence
even if it tore his flesh.

326
00:18:22,850 --> 00:18:24,390
[Ho-yeol] That's what I think.

327
00:18:25,140 --> 00:18:28,230
-[mysterious music plays]
-[soldiers chanting]

328
00:18:28,850 --> 00:18:32,730
[Ho-yeol] He was determined to climb down
a mountain to run away.

329
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:34,570
STOP THE REDEVELOPMENT

330
00:18:34,650 --> 00:18:36,240
He was even determined

331
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:42,070
to steal clothes
from a civilian household.

332
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:43,530
[in English] Okay?

333
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:48,500
[in Hangul] People as determined
as Heo Chi-do run away with a purpose.

334
00:18:49,710 --> 00:18:50,920
A very clear one at that.

335
00:18:53,290 --> 00:18:54,250
Like what?

336
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:57,170
Mm.
[sucks teeth]

337
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:58,300
Let's ask.

338
00:18:58,380 --> 00:18:59,630
[woman 1] Who are you?

339
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:06,850
Oh, hello. We're the military police.

340
00:19:07,720 --> 00:19:09,890
[Ho-yeol] Is this Mr. Heo Chi-do's house?

341
00:19:10,890 --> 00:19:12,190
Heo who?

342
00:19:15,860 --> 00:19:17,320
Ah.

343
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:18,490
[door opens]

344
00:19:18,570 --> 00:19:21,160
This is probably it. Heo Chi-do, right?

345
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:25,030
This place is registered
under his grandmother's name.

346
00:19:25,870 --> 00:19:29,620
Gosh, she really should move.
It's dangerous here.

347
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:31,500
Ma'am.

348
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:36,040
[Ho-yeol] Gosh, I guess he was
raised by his grandmother.

349
00:19:36,130 --> 00:19:37,130
[woman 1] Ma'am.

350
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:41,340
Goodness. Did you wet your pants again?

351
00:19:42,130 --> 00:19:43,180
Is it spring?

352
00:19:44,090 --> 00:19:45,470
Did the flowers bloom?

353
00:19:45,550 --> 00:19:46,640
[woman 1] Goodness.

354
00:19:48,930 --> 00:19:50,100
No, it's okay. Don't.

355
00:19:50,180 --> 00:19:51,560
It's okay.

356
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:52,520
Goodness.

357
00:19:56,980 --> 00:19:58,110
Chi-do!

358
00:19:58,730 --> 00:20:01,490
My goodness, my baby.

359
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:05,410
-No, I'm not Chi-do.
-Goodness, when did you get here?

360
00:20:05,490 --> 00:20:07,620
Did you eat?

361
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:08,790
My goodness.

362
00:20:08,870 --> 00:20:11,080
[woman 1]
She must think you're her grandson.

363
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:14,960
-[woman 2] Do you want some kimchi stew?
-But why are you looking for her grandson?

364
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:16,250
Is something wrong?

365
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:20,010
Well, Sergeant Heo Chi-do…

366
00:20:21,010 --> 00:20:22,220
Chi-do?

367
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:25,890
What?

368
00:20:28,010 --> 00:20:31,640
Well, he…

369
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:36,150
We're currently giving gifts

370
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:38,610
to model soldiers.

371
00:20:38,690 --> 00:20:40,110
"Model soldiers"?

372
00:20:40,190 --> 00:20:43,200
[Jun-ho] Sergeant Heo is on the list.

373
00:20:44,030 --> 00:20:47,030
We're planning to surprise
the soldiers' families

374
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:50,490
with the gifts instead of handing them out
to the soldiers.

375
00:20:50,580 --> 00:20:51,410
[woman 1] I see.

376
00:20:51,910 --> 00:20:54,920
-That's great. You must be proud, ma'am.
-[woman 2] My gosh.

377
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:57,710
My goodness. Well done, my little puppy.

378
00:21:02,420 --> 00:21:03,380
Jun-ho.

379
00:21:04,510 --> 00:21:05,630
-Yes?
-[sniffles]

380
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:06,640
What was that?

381
00:21:07,390 --> 00:21:09,010
Can I get a surprise gift too?

382
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:12,640
I just felt like she might worry.

383
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:13,890
Why?

384
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,560
You're pitying her.

385
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:18,190
Sick people hate it when you pity them.

386
00:21:19,980 --> 00:21:20,940
I'm sorry, sir.

387
00:21:22,230 --> 00:21:25,990
Stop empathizing too much, okay?

388
00:21:29,030 --> 00:21:30,740
[clatters]

389
00:21:30,830 --> 00:21:32,830
[man 1] That's the only house left.

390
00:21:32,910 --> 00:21:34,200
[man 2] Hey.

391
00:21:34,290 --> 00:21:36,370
I thought we just needed
to clean this place.

392
00:21:36,460 --> 00:21:39,250
[man 1]
We still need to deal with that place.

393
00:21:40,090 --> 00:21:41,090
What should we do?

394
00:21:41,710 --> 00:21:44,340
What do you mean? What can we do?

395
00:21:44,420 --> 00:21:47,260
Hey! Go hang somewhere else, okay?

396
00:21:47,340 --> 00:21:48,760
Stop getting in the way!

397
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:51,470
We're not here to get in your way.

398
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,520
We're here to visit someone.

399
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:56,060
Who? That crazy broad in that tiny house?

400
00:21:57,310 --> 00:21:58,400
Excuse me.

401
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,650
[man 1] How do you know her?

402
00:22:00,230 --> 00:22:02,570
I heard she has a grandson. Are you him?

403
00:22:02,650 --> 00:22:04,440
[puffs]

404
00:22:04,530 --> 00:22:07,490
-Yes, I'm that grandson, you asshole.
-Are you insane?

405
00:22:07,570 --> 00:22:09,200
Okay, we got it.

406
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:11,740
I'm sorry to bother you guys. Let's go.

407
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:15,000
-[man 2] Come here.
-[man 1] What are you doing? Pick that up.

408
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:16,500
Hey!

409
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:19,460
♪ Yogurt lady ♪

410
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:22,250
♪ Can I have some yogurt? ♪

411
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:25,130
[man 1 groans]

412
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:27,670
[light music plays]

413
00:22:30,430 --> 00:22:32,550
Hello, may we have a word with you?

414
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:34,180
You know Heo Chi-do, right?

415
00:22:35,810 --> 00:22:36,640
[man] Well…

416
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:39,440
I haven't seen him in a while.

417
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:40,560
The thing is,

418
00:22:41,230 --> 00:22:43,110
he suddenly dropped out
and joined the army.

419
00:22:43,190 --> 00:22:45,570
So a lot of businesses were looking
for new part-timers.

420
00:22:45,650 --> 00:22:46,690
Wait.

421
00:22:46,780 --> 00:22:51,490
What do you mean
they were looking for new part-timers?

422
00:22:51,570 --> 00:22:55,160
Well, Chi-do got into college
with the highest grades,

423
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:58,500
so he got scholarships
from both the government and the school.

424
00:22:59,330 --> 00:23:03,290
But that wasn't enough,
so he worked part-time

425
00:23:03,380 --> 00:23:06,380
as a cashier, librarian,
and other jobs outside of school.

426
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:10,430
That's around when Heo Chi-do
joined the army,

427
00:23:10,510 --> 00:23:13,260
and his grandmother was diagnosed
with dementia.

428
00:23:13,850 --> 00:23:16,350
About Heo Chi-do,

429
00:23:16,430 --> 00:23:19,810
did he gamble in college by any chance?

430
00:23:19,890 --> 00:23:22,810
"Gamble"? Chi-do?

431
00:23:23,980 --> 00:23:26,690
No, he wasn't like that at all.

432
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:30,320
I think you're mistaken.
He's a very diligent guy.

433
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:33,280
What a mystery.

434
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:37,910
Then by any chance…

435
00:23:40,290 --> 00:23:41,370
have you seen this?

436
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:47,460
[Jun-ho] There are three doors.
Two of them lead to nothing.

437
00:23:47,550 --> 00:23:48,840
You pick one,

438
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:51,260
then I think you discard one or something.

439
00:23:51,340 --> 00:23:52,800
This is the Monty Hall problem.

440
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,300
It was Chi-do's favorite.

441
00:23:55,720 --> 00:23:58,310
[stammers]
Monty what? What is that?

442
00:23:58,390 --> 00:24:01,480
[mysterious music plays]

443
00:24:02,390 --> 00:24:05,400
[Chi-do]
The answer is to change your decision.

444
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:08,650
Come and explain.

445
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:14,450
-[chuckles]
-[students] Ooh.

446
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:18,370
This is based on statistics.

447
00:24:20,330 --> 00:24:24,370
Let's say you pick a door
among these three.

448
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:27,290
There's a one third chance
that you might pick the right one.

449
00:24:27,380 --> 00:24:29,710
THE MONTY HALL PROBLEM

450
00:24:33,010 --> 00:24:36,800
But when you find out one of them is wrong
and choose a different door,

451
00:24:37,470 --> 00:24:39,390
that doesn't leave you
with a 50-50 chance.

452
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:43,350
It's two thirds.

453
00:24:44,690 --> 00:24:47,400
The variable of finding out
whether or not it's a wrong door

454
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:52,400
is influenced by and can turn out
differently based on your initial choice.

455
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:55,570
Therefore, the answer
is to change your decision.

456
00:24:57,070 --> 00:24:58,030
You're right.

457
00:24:58,660 --> 00:25:01,240
[students applaud, cheer]

458
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:07,170
A change in variables changes everything.

459
00:25:07,250 --> 00:25:10,550
But most people make mistakes
by refusing to switch their decisions

460
00:25:10,630 --> 00:25:13,380
due to distrust or fear.

461
00:25:13,470 --> 00:25:14,760
Then…

462
00:25:15,970 --> 00:25:20,390
what if we substitute this
to our everyday lives?

463
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:24,390
[professor]
Then that would add one more variable.

464
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:30,940
UNCERTAINTY

465
00:25:31,020 --> 00:25:32,320
"Uncertainty."

466
00:25:33,240 --> 00:25:35,990
That's because our minds and emotions

467
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,700
aren't based on probabilities.

468
00:25:38,780 --> 00:25:41,700
[mysterious music playing continues]

469
00:25:44,580 --> 00:25:47,330
-Call us if you hear from him.
-Okay, bye.

470
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:52,380
Jun-ho, I didn't get
a word he said in there.

471
00:25:52,460 --> 00:25:56,300
So if you choose the wrong door,
does that invalidate the door you chose?

472
00:25:56,380 --> 00:25:59,090
-Or does it validate…
-You don't get it either, do you?

473
00:25:59,180 --> 00:26:00,140
Excuse me.

474
00:26:02,260 --> 00:26:03,970
I think you should take this call.

475
00:26:07,060 --> 00:26:08,730
[Chi-do] You should stop looking for me.

476
00:26:08,810 --> 00:26:09,650
Heo Chi-do?

477
00:26:09,730 --> 00:26:11,560
I'll return when it's time.

478
00:26:11,650 --> 00:26:13,780
Hey, we want to go back to our unit too.

479
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:17,990
But we can only do that once we find you.

480
00:26:18,070 --> 00:26:21,370
You don't get it, do you? Just go.

481
00:26:21,450 --> 00:26:23,410
-Go where?
-[line beeps]

482
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:27,710
How did he know we were here?

483
00:26:34,300 --> 00:26:35,420
[man gasps]

484
00:26:36,510 --> 00:26:38,840
-[quirky music plays]
-Heo Chi-do…

485
00:26:40,890 --> 00:26:42,100
Heo Chi-do…

486
00:26:42,180 --> 00:26:43,430
[man grunts]

487
00:26:45,060 --> 00:26:48,100
[quirky music playing continues]

488
00:26:48,180 --> 00:26:49,190
[Ho-yeol] Sergeant Heo!

489
00:26:50,020 --> 00:26:52,020
[pants]

490
00:26:53,940 --> 00:26:55,570
[both heaving]

491
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:00,910
[Ho-yeol]
Why is your school so big, Chi-do?

492
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,950
[Chi-do pants]

493
00:27:04,030 --> 00:27:06,580
[Ho-yeol heaves]

494
00:27:10,620 --> 00:27:13,460
[indistinct chatter]

495
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,920
[crowd exclaim]

496
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:20,090
[quirky music playing]

497
00:27:24,140 --> 00:27:25,640
[Ho-yeol] Don't go uphill!

498
00:27:41,450 --> 00:27:42,660
Chi-do!

499
00:27:43,240 --> 00:27:44,450
Heo Chi-do!

500
00:27:45,490 --> 00:27:47,450
Chi-do, let's go home.

501
00:27:47,540 --> 00:27:50,830
Checkmate! Come on!

502
00:27:50,910 --> 00:27:52,040
Is this the right place?

503
00:27:52,960 --> 00:27:53,880
Wait.

504
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:57,000
I think I just heard something.

505
00:28:00,090 --> 00:28:02,430
[creaks]

506
00:28:05,930 --> 00:28:07,510
[screams]

507
00:28:08,100 --> 00:28:09,470
-Who are you guys?
-[girl] What is it?

508
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:11,770
[girl 1]Why are there men here?

509
00:28:11,850 --> 00:28:14,650
[girl 2] Who are they?
Why are these guys here?

510
00:28:14,730 --> 00:28:16,650
[Ho-yeol whispers] Heo Chi-do, that punk.

511
00:28:17,900 --> 00:28:19,900
I'm sorry. I really am.

512
00:28:19,980 --> 00:28:21,490
-[Jun-ho] It's all a misunderstanding.
-[Ho-yeol] We're not perverts.

513
00:28:21,570 --> 00:28:22,950
[Jun-ho] Please, don't curse at us.

514
00:28:23,030 --> 00:28:24,990
-[Ho-yeol and Jun-ho] We're sorry.
-[sighs]

515
00:28:27,370 --> 00:28:30,250
Goodness, my gallbladder.
[groans]

516
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:33,370
If you smoke when your gallbladder hurts,

517
00:28:33,460 --> 00:28:35,460
-your bile--
-Shut your mouth, you pervert.

518
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,210
It was a trap…

519
00:28:38,290 --> 00:28:40,130
Your face is a trap, you punk.

520
00:28:41,050 --> 00:28:43,930
I can't believe I received a complaint
from a women's dorm.

521
00:28:45,970 --> 00:28:47,680
-I'm sorry, sir.
-I'm sorry, sir.

522
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:48,600
Get out.

523
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:55,270
[dramatic music plays]

524
