597
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:35,700
Are we playing soldiers here?

598
00:32:36,870 --> 00:32:39,370
-Hey, newbie. Stand here.
-Private Kang Byeong-su, sir.

599
00:32:39,450 --> 00:32:41,160
[soldier] Hurry up, you punk.

600
00:32:41,870 --> 00:32:43,210
Jun-ho.

601
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:45,880
Private An Jun-ho, sir.

602
00:32:47,090 --> 00:32:48,250
[Jang-soo] Hit him.

603
00:32:51,300 --> 00:32:52,670
[sighs]

604
00:32:55,130 --> 00:32:58,970
[grunts]
Private Kang Byeong-su, sir.

605
00:32:59,810 --> 00:33:00,680
Jun-ho.

606
00:33:02,100 --> 00:33:03,520
Private An Jun-ho, sir.

607
00:33:04,480 --> 00:33:05,480
Hit him.

608
00:33:08,060 --> 00:33:13,360
[grunting]
Private Kang Byeong-su, sir.

609
00:33:14,490 --> 00:33:15,610
[Jang-soo] Jun-ho.

610
00:33:16,110 --> 00:33:17,740
-[sniffles]
-[Byeong-su pants]

611
00:33:17,820 --> 00:33:19,530
Do you think I'll stop if you don't do it?

612
00:33:20,950 --> 00:33:22,830
[shaky breath]

613
00:33:22,910 --> 00:33:23,910
[Jang-soo] Hit him.

614
00:33:24,830 --> 00:33:28,630
[ominous music plays]

615
00:33:30,420 --> 00:33:34,170
Gosh, you guys are so loud.
What's with all this ruckus?

616
00:33:34,260 --> 00:33:36,130
There's your fucking boyfriend.

617
00:33:37,220 --> 00:33:38,720
[Jang-soo speaks Hangul]

618
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:42,140
You prick. You have no damn respect
for your damn seniors.

619
00:33:42,220 --> 00:33:44,180
-[Ho-yeol] Follow me.
-[Jun-ho] Corporal Han, wait…

620
00:33:44,270 --> 00:33:46,270
-Corporal Han, we were just--
-Shut up, okay?

621
00:33:46,350 --> 00:33:47,400
-Come here.
-Corporal Han.

622
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:48,810
[Jun-ho grunts]

623
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:50,400
[door creaks, closes]

624
00:33:52,230 --> 00:33:54,440
Corporal Han, sir. What's gotten into you?

625
00:33:55,650 --> 00:33:56,490
I just…

626
00:33:58,740 --> 00:34:00,870
Are your seniors

627
00:34:00,950 --> 00:34:03,790
some kind of a joke to you, you punk?

628
00:34:04,910 --> 00:34:07,540
You asshole! I can't believe this!

629
00:34:07,620 --> 00:34:10,170
Stand up straight.
Clench your teeth! You punk! Shut up!

630
00:34:10,250 --> 00:34:12,130
What did you do wrong? Tell me, you punk!

631
00:34:12,210 --> 00:34:13,920
[grunts]

632
00:34:14,010 --> 00:34:15,300
[Jun-ho] I'm sorry, sir!

633
00:34:15,380 --> 00:34:16,380
I'm sorry, sir!

634
00:34:17,510 --> 00:34:20,470
[Jun-ho yelps]

635
00:34:21,350 --> 00:34:23,890
Let's stop here.
[laughs]

636
00:34:24,890 --> 00:34:27,980
Corporal Han is killing him in there.

637
00:34:28,060 --> 00:34:31,690
I guess that asshole still wants respect
even though he's hardly here.

638
00:34:31,770 --> 00:34:33,230
[soldier chuckles]

639
00:34:33,860 --> 00:34:35,070
Let's go sleep.

640
00:34:35,150 --> 00:34:37,150
Gosh, that startled me.

641
00:34:46,290 --> 00:34:47,620
I think they're gone.

642
00:34:49,420 --> 00:34:51,290
[object thuds]

643
00:34:52,250 --> 00:34:54,340
[sighs]
Jun-ho.

644
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:58,590
Stop getting yourself in trouble here.

645
00:34:59,510 --> 00:35:03,300
If you keep this up, they'll harass you
even after Jang-soo is discharged.

646
00:35:03,890 --> 00:35:05,220
I'm sorry, sir.

647
00:35:05,310 --> 00:35:07,810
[Ho-yeol] Don't be. You did nothing wrong.

648
00:35:07,890 --> 00:35:10,520
What's the point of bringing back
all those deserters?

649
00:35:10,600 --> 00:35:12,560
All that bullshit exists even here.

650
00:35:12,650 --> 00:35:14,690
[clicks tongue]
I totally get why they desert.

651
00:35:17,070 --> 00:35:18,070
What are you doing?

652
00:35:19,070 --> 00:35:20,110
Just a second, sir.

653
00:35:21,070 --> 00:35:23,280
[sighs]
You're like Sherlock.

654
00:35:23,910 --> 00:35:26,120
[Ho-yeol] What are you trying
to investigate this time?

655
00:35:29,210 --> 00:35:30,410
[scribbles]

656
00:35:35,380 --> 00:35:37,960
[soft percussive music plays]

657
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:42,260
His first choice was to quit college
and join the army.

658
00:35:43,550 --> 00:35:45,300
"Hey, Mr. Heo.

659
00:35:45,390 --> 00:35:47,770
You abandoned your grandmother
by joining the army, right?"

660
00:35:50,020 --> 00:35:51,810
[Jun-ho] If he abandoned his grandmother,

661
00:35:54,020 --> 00:35:56,730
he wouldn't have had to worry about
making the wrong choice.

662
00:35:57,530 --> 00:35:59,240
-You're right.
-But…

663
00:35:59,990 --> 00:36:02,990
what if he was trying
to protect his grandmother?

664
00:36:04,200 --> 00:36:05,580
Ah.

665
00:36:06,580 --> 00:36:10,200
[Ho-yeol] So was the variable
his grandmother's dementia?

666
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:14,710
No, he joined the army
after she got dementia.

667
00:36:15,290 --> 00:36:16,130
Okay.

668
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:18,050
What if the variable…

669
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:21,340
was the demolition of his house?

670
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:26,180
[Jun-ho] Okay. One.

671
00:36:26,850 --> 00:36:30,100
He joined the army
to protect his grandmother. Two.

672
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:34,690
He suddenly found out his house
was going to be demolished.

673
00:36:36,650 --> 00:36:37,730
Three.

674
00:36:39,070 --> 00:36:40,860
So maybe he abandoned the army

675
00:36:40,940 --> 00:36:43,360
and chose to go to a place

676
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:47,870
that would give him a better chance
at protecting his grandmother.

677
00:36:47,950 --> 00:36:49,080
[scoffs]

678
00:36:50,790 --> 00:36:51,950
-Desertion.
-Desertion.

679
00:36:52,790 --> 00:36:53,870
Wait a minute.

680
00:36:54,870 --> 00:36:56,960
Heo Chi-do called us.

681
00:36:58,290 --> 00:37:00,960
How did he know who we were?

682
00:37:01,050 --> 00:37:02,760
[deep inhale]

683
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:04,970
[ominous music plays]

684
00:37:06,220 --> 00:37:09,600
[ominous music playing continues]

685
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:12,560
-What? What is it?
-[sighs]

686
00:37:12,640 --> 00:37:14,020
I can't believe I missed that.

687
00:37:17,650 --> 00:37:19,650
You damn perverts.

688
00:37:19,730 --> 00:37:22,110
-Private An Jun-ho, sir.
-Corporal Han Ho-yeol, sir.

689
00:37:22,820 --> 00:37:25,030
How long has it been
since they've returned?

690
00:37:25,740 --> 00:37:28,740
-It's been 14 hours and 25 minutes, sir.
-Did you hear that?

691
00:37:29,580 --> 00:37:30,740
It's only been that long.

692
00:37:30,830 --> 00:37:32,080
We found a way…

693
00:37:32,790 --> 00:37:34,580
to bring Heo Chi-do back.

694
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:36,420
Was it Jun-ho's idea again?

695
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:38,540
Are you sure?

696
00:37:38,630 --> 00:37:41,090
We're extremely enthusiastic.

697
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:44,800
Gosh, my damn gallbladder hurt just now.
I think I have gallstones.

698
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:46,050
I think…

699
00:37:47,130 --> 00:37:50,010
we have more than
a 50 percent probability.

700
00:37:50,100 --> 00:37:52,140
[Beom-gu]
I'll kill you only 50 percent then.

701
00:37:52,220 --> 00:37:53,560
[clicks tongue]

702
00:37:54,770 --> 00:37:56,310
[exhales]

703
00:38:00,440 --> 00:38:04,190
[mysterious music plays]

704
00:38:08,990 --> 00:38:11,080
[man 1] Let's hurry this up and go home.

705
00:38:11,160 --> 00:38:13,790
[indistinct chatter]

706
00:38:13,870 --> 00:38:15,870
[man 2] You punk, do a proper job!

707
00:38:18,580 --> 00:38:20,670
[man 3] Hey, let's eat!

708
00:38:20,750 --> 00:38:23,300
[indistinct chatter]

709
00:38:26,050 --> 00:38:26,970
[man 1] Hey!

710
00:38:28,970 --> 00:38:30,260
Let's eat.

711
00:38:30,340 --> 00:38:32,390
[pants]

712
00:38:35,310 --> 00:38:36,600
[Ho-yeol] Thank you for the meal.

713
00:38:39,900 --> 00:38:41,480
[sighs]

714
00:38:41,560 --> 00:38:45,280
What's wrong? Does the food outside
taste the same as the food in the army?

715
00:38:50,160 --> 00:38:51,950
Gosh, this is so exhausting.

716
00:38:53,450 --> 00:38:55,120
How did you manage to work here
for months?

717
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:56,500
Sergeant Heo Chi-do.

718
00:39:02,130 --> 00:39:03,250
Shit.

719
00:39:04,250 --> 00:39:05,590
I'm with the military police.

720
00:39:09,300 --> 00:39:10,720
You fucking…

721
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:12,510
[grunts]

722
00:39:12,600 --> 00:39:14,180
[Ho-yeol] Sergeant Heo Chi-do.

723
00:39:14,760 --> 00:39:17,100
You're under emergency arrest
without a warrant for desertion.

724
00:39:17,180 --> 00:39:18,390
[Chi-do groans]

725
00:39:18,980 --> 00:39:20,690
[pants]

726
00:39:20,770 --> 00:39:21,850
How…

727
00:39:23,060 --> 00:39:25,270
How?
[grunts]

728
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:28,030
-[pants]
-[cuffs click]

729
00:39:28,610 --> 00:39:32,740
[Jun-ho] A place where you could protect
your grandmother from close-by.

730
00:39:32,820 --> 00:39:35,080
[somber music plays]

731
00:39:36,410 --> 00:39:39,370
And this is that place.

732
00:39:42,790 --> 00:39:46,550
[Ho-yeol] Why do you need money so badly

733
00:39:47,670 --> 00:39:49,670
for you to even demolish your own house?

734
00:39:50,590 --> 00:39:53,590
[heavy breathing]

735
00:39:53,680 --> 00:39:56,060
I need to send my grandmother
to a sanitarium.

736
00:39:57,470 --> 00:39:59,020
[Chi-do breathes heavily]

737
00:39:59,100 --> 00:40:02,940
[somber music playing continues]

738
00:40:03,850 --> 00:40:06,480
[Jun-ho]
Even if your house disappears tomorrow…

739
00:40:07,070 --> 00:40:09,110
FIGHTING AGAINST FORCED EVICTION

740
00:40:09,190 --> 00:40:11,150
You climbed over a barbed-wire fence…

741
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:13,030
[alarm blares]

742
00:40:14,620 --> 00:40:16,580
[pants]

743
00:40:19,450 --> 00:40:21,710
…walked down the mountain
for over ten hours,

744
00:40:22,870 --> 00:40:25,790
and ran away without getting caught
by the search troops.

745
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:28,170
[panting continues]

746
00:40:30,460 --> 00:40:33,720
[Jun-ho] Was the probability to succeed
a hundred percent?

747
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:38,680
[somber music plays]

748
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:43,690
[Chi-do] I'm sorry,

749
00:40:44,770 --> 00:40:46,730
but can I visit my grandmother
before I go?

750
00:40:49,820 --> 00:40:53,280
[somber music playing continues]

751
00:40:59,700 --> 00:41:00,700
Flowers…

752
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:03,710
Did the flowers bloom?

753
00:41:04,330 --> 00:41:06,290
[sniffs, exhales]

754
00:41:06,380 --> 00:41:08,460
I need to go see flowers.

755
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:12,420
[tranquil music playing]

756
00:41:22,850 --> 00:41:24,020
Grandma.

757
00:41:32,610 --> 00:41:35,490
[gasps]
My goodness, Chi-do.

758
00:41:35,570 --> 00:41:37,820
My goodness, my sweetheart.

759
00:41:37,910 --> 00:41:40,370
My goodness, my little puppy.

760
00:41:40,450 --> 00:41:43,080
Goodness gracious. My goodness.

761
00:41:43,160 --> 00:41:46,210
Why do you look so worn out?
You're only in college.

762
00:41:46,790 --> 00:41:50,670
[woman] You're the pride
of this neighborhood. My goodness.

763
00:41:50,750 --> 00:41:53,510
You don't skip your meals, do you?

764
00:41:54,090 --> 00:41:56,380
Didn't you miss me?

765
00:41:58,180 --> 00:42:00,800
What took you so long to visit?

766
00:42:01,510 --> 00:42:03,970
You're busy with your studies, aren't you?

767
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:06,810
You should take it easy.

768
00:42:07,390 --> 00:42:10,310
You're all I have left now.

769
00:42:11,520 --> 00:42:12,440
Chi-do…

770
00:42:13,440 --> 00:42:15,780
I'll come back in spring, Grandma.

771
00:42:22,790 --> 00:42:24,370
Let's go see flowers together.

772
00:42:26,210 --> 00:42:30,000
[dramatic music plays]

773
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:54,190
[dramatic music playing continues]

774
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:02,950
[wind gust]

775
00:43:06,370 --> 00:43:08,620
[car horn honks in distance]

776
00:43:08,710 --> 00:43:10,170
I have a question.

777
00:43:12,540 --> 00:43:14,590
How was joining the army

778
00:43:14,670 --> 00:43:17,880
a way to protect your grandmother?

779
00:43:25,180 --> 00:43:26,640
Back then, I was worried…

780
00:43:31,650 --> 00:43:33,810
I might think of doing something bad.

781
00:43:37,570 --> 00:43:40,030
Gosh, this is so complicated.

782
00:43:41,110 --> 00:43:42,110
[sighs]

783
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:43,490
This is all because of…

784
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:45,830
that Centermony…

785
00:43:45,910 --> 00:43:47,450
The Monty Hall problem.

786
00:43:47,540 --> 00:43:48,910
Right. That's to blame.

787
00:43:50,330 --> 00:43:51,500
[scoffs]

788
00:43:54,170 --> 00:43:55,710
How much more do you need to make?

789
00:43:57,050 --> 00:43:58,050
[Chi-do] Sorry, sir?

790
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:06,560
About two more months.
Then I can sign her into a hospital.

791
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:08,060
I still don't get

792
00:44:08,720 --> 00:44:11,310
the Monty Hall problem, or whatever it is.

793
00:44:12,480 --> 00:44:14,360
-But I'm guessing…
-[cuffs clink]

794
00:44:15,440 --> 00:44:17,480
…it's something like this, right?

795
00:44:18,070 --> 00:44:21,570
[Ho-yeol] It's something about variables.

796
00:44:21,650 --> 00:44:22,860
That's what it is, right?

797
00:44:23,450 --> 00:44:25,070
Giving someone a chance to decide?

798
00:44:26,410 --> 00:44:28,580
-There.
-[cuffs clink]

799
00:44:29,830 --> 00:44:30,700
Go.

800
00:44:32,540 --> 00:44:34,960
Make sure you send your grandmother
to a sanitarium

801
00:44:36,170 --> 00:44:37,420
and then turn yourself in.

802
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:45,340
[dramatic music plays]

803
00:44:50,180 --> 00:44:51,520
Thank you.

804
00:44:59,900 --> 00:45:02,650
[sobs]
Thank you.

805
00:45:07,830 --> 00:45:08,870
Thank you.

806
00:45:09,490 --> 00:45:11,750
[sobbing continues]

807
00:45:13,830 --> 00:45:16,500
[dramatic music playing continues]

808
00:45:21,420 --> 00:45:23,800
You lost him? How?

809
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:26,430
[Ho-yeol sighs]
We lost him outside.

810
00:45:28,720 --> 00:45:29,810
Okay.

811
00:45:31,060 --> 00:45:33,350
Good work. Now get back here.

812
00:45:33,430 --> 00:45:35,100
[deep inhale]

813
00:45:35,850 --> 00:45:37,020
[scoffs]

814
00:45:41,020 --> 00:45:42,150
Mm.

815
00:45:50,240 --> 00:45:51,370
Why did you let him go?

816
00:45:52,410 --> 00:45:53,410
What?

817
00:45:55,540 --> 00:45:57,040
I just felt like it.

818
00:45:57,710 --> 00:45:59,540
I have problems controlling my impulses.

819
00:46:02,210 --> 00:46:04,380
-Mm.
-What if he doesn't turn himself in?

820
00:46:08,390 --> 00:46:09,890
Isn't it a 50-50 chance anyway?

821
00:46:11,140 --> 00:46:12,680
Either he does or he doesn't.

822
00:46:15,100 --> 00:46:16,230
Isn't it two thirds?

823
00:46:19,440 --> 00:46:21,650
[tranquil music plays]

824
00:46:23,400 --> 00:46:26,650
[tranquil music playing continues]

825
00:46:38,250 --> 00:46:40,000
[keys clack]

826
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:43,550
[line rings]

827
00:46:47,420 --> 00:46:48,510
[Jun-ho's mother] Hello?

828
00:46:50,220 --> 00:46:51,760
[Jun-ho] Mom, it's me.

829
00:46:52,510 --> 00:46:53,760
Hey, Jun-ho.

830
00:46:55,470 --> 00:46:56,480
Hey.

831
00:47:00,980 --> 00:47:02,730
Did you eat?

832
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:06,110
[upbeat music plays]

833
00:47:07,440 --> 00:47:08,860
Wake up! Everyone, wake up!

834
00:47:09,490 --> 00:47:11,820
[soldiers grunt]

835
00:47:14,830 --> 00:47:16,200
What is it, sir?

836
00:47:17,200 --> 00:47:19,040
[pants]

837
00:47:20,250 --> 00:47:21,540
I think Cho Suk-bong…

838
00:47:23,590 --> 00:47:24,750
deserted the army.

839
00:47:29,550 --> 00:47:30,720
PRIVATE CHO SUK-BONG

840
00:47:33,930 --> 00:47:37,350
[theme music plays]

841
00:47:40,520 --> 00:47:43,610
GUEST APPEARANCE BY KWON HAE-HYO

842
00:50:14,460 --> 00:50:16,090
[music ends]